HEADWORD: Pederasty
<hw>Ped"er*as`ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>paiderasti`a</grk>: cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧d⟦eacute⟧rastie</ets>.]</ety> <def>Sexual activity between
two males; sodomy; the ⟦ldquo⟧crime against nature⟦rdquo⟧; -- used
especially when one partner is a boy.</def> <note>The term ⟦ldquo⟧crime
against nature⟦rdquo⟧ to refer to homosexual activity is now (2002)
seldom used except by religious conservatives. It was in the 1913
Webster, and is left here for historical purposes.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

